summary:
{
"headline": "Weight Stigma and Health Behaviors: New Research Findings",
"body": "New research highlights the negative impact of weight stigma on health behaviors. The study found that weight stigma is associated with poorer health behaviors such as disordered eating, comfort eating, alcohol use, and sleep disturbance. The findings suggest that weight stigma may be a barrier to healthy habits, independent of body mass index (BMI). This research sheds light on the importance of reducing weight stigma to improve population health."
}

